Package com.purnendu.quizo.models

Class Attempt

java.lang.Object
com.purnendu.quizo.models.Attempt
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.os.Parcelable
public class Attempt extends Object implements android.os.Parcelable
Represents a single quiz attempt by a user in the Quizo application. This class is designed as a Room Entity for database persistence, storing details about when the attempt was made, the subject, performance, and points. The createdTime serves as the PrimaryKey. It also implements Parcelable for efficient data transfer between Android components.

Key fields include:

  • createdTime: The timestamp (in milliseconds) when the quiz attempt was recorded, serving as the primary key.
  • subject: The topic of the quiz (e.g., "Math", "Geography").
  • correct: The number of questions answered correctly.
  • incorrect: The number of questions answered incorrectly.
  • earned: The points earned from this specific quiz attempt.
  • email: The email of the user who made this attempt.
  • overallPoints: The user's total accumulated points after this attempt.
